{
  "texts": [
    "In IoA, each newcomer agent provides a self-reported capability profile during registration, detailing its foundational model characteristics, available tools, and functional expertise [7], [9].",
    "For instance, an agent might declare its profile as \"{model: \"GPT-4o\", tools: [\"Web Browser\", \"Code Executor\"], description: \"Specialized in QA tasks\"}\".",
    "While self-reporting facilitates rapid onboarding, it is inherently prone to inaccuracies or overstatements.",
    "• Systematic Capability Verification.",
    "To enhance reliability, gateway agents could perform capability verification using standardized evaluation suites to objectively assess critical competencies."
  ]
}